-- Colombian Stock Movers: Bolsa de Valores, Pacific Rubiales Rise
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-02-23T16:25:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/colombian-stock-movers-bolsa-de-valores-pacific-rubiales-rise.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:09 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 1.6 percent to 14,801.64, while the
Colcap Index gained 0.5 percent to 1,712.46.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia SA  (BVC CB), the operator of
 Colombia ’s main stock exchange, rose 0.9 percent to 32.3 pesos.
The company will pay a 2012 dividend of 1.52 pesos per share,
including an extraordinary dividend of 0.46 pesos per share,
according to a regulatory filing today. That is a 64 percent
increase from last year’s dividend, the filing said.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 5.3 percent
to 51,300 pesos, a six-month high. Oil and natural-gas reserves
at the end of last year were 52 percent higher than the year
before, driven by an 83 percent exploration success rate,
according to a statement on the company’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
